# Multi-Tenant Sales Dashboard - Complete Project Summary

## üì¶ What You've Received

A complete, production-ready React + Vite application with **32 files** organized in a professional structure.

## üìã Complete File List

### 1. Configuration Files (7 files)
- `package.json` - Project dependencies and npm scripts
- `vite.config.js` - Vite build configuration
- `tailwind.config.js` - Tailwind CSS configuration
- `postcss.config.js` - PostCSS configuration
- `.env.example` - Environment variables template
- `.gitignore` - Git ignore rules
- `index.html` - HTML entry point

### 2. React Entry Points (2 files)
- `src/main.jsx` - React DOM render entry
- `src/App.jsx` - Root React component

### 3. Global Styles (1 file)
- `src/styles/globals.css` - Global CSS styles

### 4. State Management (1 file)
- `src/context/TenantContext.jsx` - Global tenant context provider

### 5. Custom Hooks (1 file)
- `src/hooks/useTenant.js` - Custom hook to access tenant context

### 6. Utilities (3 files)
- `src/utils/permissions.js` - Role-based permission definitions
- `src/utils/mockData.js` - Mock data for both tenants
- `src/utils/constants.js` - Application constants

### 7. Header Components (3 files)
- `src/components/Header/Header.jsx` - Main header
- `src/components/Header/TenantSwitcher.jsx` - Tenant switcher dropdown
- `src/components/Header/RoleSwitcher.jsx` - Role switcher dropdown

### 8. Leads Module (3 files)
- `src/components/Leads/LeadsModule.jsx` - Leads container
- `src/components/Leads/LeadsTable.jsx` - Leads table display
- `src/components/Leads/StatusFilter.jsx` - Status filter dropdown

### 9. Call Logs Module (2 files)
- `src/components/CallLogs/CallLogsModule.jsx` - Call logs container
- `src/components/CallLogs/CallLogsTable.jsx` - Call logs table

### 10. Common Components (3 files)
- `src/components/Common/LoadingState.jsx` - Loading indicator
- `src/components/Common/EmptyState.jsx` - Empty state display
- `src/components/Common/PermissionGate.jsx` - Permission checker

### 11. Layout Components (2 files)
- `src/components/Layout/Dashboard.jsx` - Main dashboard layout
- `src/components/Layout/TabNavigation.jsx` - Tab navigation

### 12. Documentation (5 files)
- `README.md` - Complete project documentation
- `SETUP.md` - Installation and setup guide
- `ARCHITECTURE.md` - Technical architecture documentation
- `QUICK_REFERENCE.md` - Quick reference guide
- `PROJECT_STRUCTURE.txt` - Visual project structure
- `FILES_LIST.md` - Complete file listing (in artifacts)

## üöÄ Quick Start

```bash
# 1. Install dependencies
npm install

# 2. Start development server
npm run dev

# Opens at http://localhost:3000
```

## ‚ú® Key Features

### ‚úÖ Multi-Tenancy
- Switch between Organization A and B
- Complete data isolation per tenant
- Automatic UI updates on tenant switch

### ‚úÖ Role-Based Access Control
- Admin role with full access
- Agent role with read-only access
- Dynamic permission-based UI rendering

### ‚úÖ Core Modules
- **Leads Module**: View, filter, and manage leads
- **Call Logs Module**: Track call history with outcomes

### ‚úÖ User Experience
- Loading states for async operations
- Empty states when no data available
- Responsive design with Tailwind CSS
- Professional UI with icons (Lucide)

### ‚úÖ Code Quality
- Modular, reusable components
- Custom hooks for logic reusability
- Clean separation of concerns
- JSDoc comments for functions
- Performance optimizations (useMemo, useCallback)

## üìä Technology Stack

- **React 18.2** - UI library with hooks
- **Vite 5** - Lightning-fast build tool
- **Tailwind CSS 3** - Utility-first CSS framework
- **Lucide React** - Icon library
- **Context API** - State management (no Redux needed)

## üèóÔ∏è Architecture Highlights

### State Management
- Uses React Context API instead of Redux
- Simpler, cleaner, perfect for this scope
- Easy to migrate to Redux if needed later

### Component Organization
- Feature-based folder structure (Leads, CallLogs)
- Small reusable components (< 150 lines)
- Clear separation: Container vs Presentation components

### Performance Optimization
- useMemo for expensive calculations
- useCallback for function stability
- Tree-shaking with Vite
- Lazy loading ready (React.lazy + Suspense)

### Permission System
- Granular permission definitions
- Role-based permission mapping
- Runtime permission checks at component level
- PermissionGate wrapper component

